# GitHub Configuration (Optional)
# Set these environment variables to enable automatic GitHub issue creation for bug reports
#
# To generate a GitHub Personal Access Token:
# 1. Go to GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens → Tokens (classic)
# 2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Name: signal_server_bug_reporter
# 4. Select scopes: repo (full control)
# 5. Generate and copy the token
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit this file with actual values! Add .env to .gitignore

# GitHub Personal Access Token (classic) with 'repo' scope
# Example: GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# GitHub repository in format "owner/repo"
# Default: yksi7417/signal_server
GITHUB_REPO=yksi7417/signal_server

# Usage:
# 1. Copy this file to .env (do not commit .env!)
# 2. Add your GITHUB_TOKEN value
# 3. Ensure .env is in .gitignore
# 4. Restart the server
#
# If GITHUB_TOKEN is not set:
# - Bug reports will still be saved locally
# - Users will get a manual link to create GitHub issues
#
# If GITHUB_TOKEN is set:
# - Bug reports will automatically create GitHub issues
# - Issues will be labeled with "bug" and "auto-reported"
